# Monorepo Structure

Apps and packages MUST live under these paths only:

| Type | Path | Example |
|------|------|---------|
| Web app | `apps/web/<name>/` | `apps/web/dashboard/` |
| Mobile app | `apps/mobile/<name>/` | `apps/mobile/customer-app/` |
| Server | `apps/server/<name>/` | `apps/server/auth-api/` |
| Shared package | `packages/<name>/` | `packages/shared/` |
| Scripts/tools | `tools/scripts/` | `tools/scripts/deploy.sh` |
| Documentation | `docs/` | `docs/adr-001.md` |

NEVER create application or package directories outside this structure.

## When adding or removing apps/packages

Read and follow the `project-architecture` skill at `.cursor/skills/project-architecture/SKILL.md`. It contains the full step-by-step workflow including README updates and audit procedures.

## Naming

- `kebab-case` for all directory names.
- Names must be descriptive (e.g. `auth-api`, not `api2`).

## Forbidden

- Apps at the root level.
- Apps nested inside other apps.
- New top-level directories without explicit user approval.
- Skipping documentation updates after structural changes.
